  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArrayLexicon Deprecated
    Lexicon class for index-generation in Indexing.
    BiMapLexicon
    Lexicon based on Google's BiMap.
    BinaryIndexing<V extends java.lang.Number>
    Variant of Indexing class, where the IDs of the words and the frequency are stored in binary.
    HexadecimalIndexing<V extends java.lang.Number>
    Variant of Indexing class, where the IDs of the words and the frequency are stored in hexadecimal.
    Indexing<V extends java.lang.Number>
    Indexing is a class to store n-gram frequencies and probabilites in a more efficient manner.
    IndexReader<V extends java.lang.Number>
    Reader to read a dumped indexing parallelized.
    ListLexicon Deprecated
    Lexicon class for index-generation in Indexing.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    IncompleteLexiconException
    Exception to be thrown while creating indices in the Indexing class when a Lexicon was loaded before and an ID is being looked up that doesn't exist in the lexicon.
